examples.en: The problem concerns us all.
Her ill health concerns me.
He concerns himself with trivia.
Her concerns transcended local issues.
Our mother's illness concerns us.
The novel concerns three soldiers.
This study concerns the noise levels in cities.
Koch unloaded his concerns over dinner one night.
The decline in sales only validated our concerns.
He has many concerns, chief among them his health.
Her new novel is overlaid with political concerns.
Economic concerns are foremost on many voters' minds.
They feel injured by our dismissal of their concerns.
My concerns are all general  nothing specific.
The need for blood donors trumps all other concerns.
He formulated his concerns to the board of trustees.
Passenger safety overrides all of our other concerns.
This study concerns couples' expectations of marriage.
They have raised concerns about the cost of the project.
He dismissed her concerns with an airy wave of the hand.
All these concerns need to be brought out into the open.
The President needs to address the concerns of the farmers.
The parents had little interest in paltry domestic concerns.
Let's not perplex the issue further with irrelevant concerns.
The report concerns the drug traffic on the Mexican-US border.
He's too busy with immediate concerns to worry about the future.
Poor revenue figures have stoked concerns about possible layoffs.
The governor needs to address voters' concerns about the economy.
There are concerns that some players have been doctoring the ball.
He claims to be above such earthborn concerns as material comfort.
